### 🧬 STRIKE 22.2: THE DOCKER SWARM SUBSTRATE
**The Gnostic Framing:** This is the **Authority of High Availability**. It righteously `@provides: [docker-swarm-substrate, container-orchestration-ha]`. It materializes the `swarm_init.sh` ritual and sutured `deploy` edicts, enabling the project to survive the death of a physical node through service replication and VIP routing.

**Target Locus:** `shards/system/docker-swarm-substrate.scaffold`

```scaffold
# ==============================================================================
# == GNOSTIC SHARD: DOCKER-SWARM-SUBSTRATE (V-Ω-TOTALITY-V1.0)                ==
# ==============================================================================
# @description: The definitive high-availability substrate. Materializes the 
#               Docker Swarm infrastructure, enabling multi-node clustering, 
#               service replication, and zero-downtime rolling updates.
# @category: System / Substrate
# @vibe: docker-swarm, clustering, high-availability, orchestration, replication
# @provides: [docker-swarm-substrate, container-orchestration-ha, cluster-authority]
# @requires: [docker-orchestration]
# @substrate: docker
# @version: 1.0.0-Ω
# @LIF: 1,000,000x
# ==============================================================================

# --- I. THE ALTAR OF GNOSTIC WILL ---
$$ project_slug = {{ project_slug | default("resonant-swarm") }}
$$ replica_count = {{ replicas | default(3) }}

# --- II. THE SCRIPTURE OF FORM (The Swarm) ---

# [ASCENSION 1]: The Swarm Stack Definition
# This file transmutes a standard Compose file into a Swarm Stack.
docker-stack.yml :: """
version: '3.8'
services:
  app:
    image: {{ project_slug }}:latest
    networks:
      - gnostic_mesh
    deploy:
      mode: replicated
      replicas: {{ replica_count }}
      update_config:
        parallelism: 1
        delay: 10s
      restart_policy:
        condition: on-failure

networks:
  gnostic_mesh:
    driver: overlay # [ASCENSION 2]: Multi-host Overlay Network
"""

# [ASCENSION 3]: THE RITE OF IGNITION (Swarm Init)
scripts/
    swarm_ignite.sh :: """
#!/bin/bash
set -e
echo "🐝 [SWARM] Initiating Cluster Consecration..."

# Check if node is already a manager
if [ "$(docker info --format '{{"{{"}}.Swarm.LocalNodeState{{"}}"}}')" == "active" ]; then
    echo "✅ Node is already part of a Swarm. Proceeding to Strike..."
else
    # [ASCENSION 9]: Autonomic Swarm Inception
    docker swarm init --advertise-addr 127.0.0.1
    echo "✨ [RESONANT] Swarm initialized."
fi

# Materialize the Overlay Mesh
docker network create --driver overlay --attachable gnostic_mesh 2>/dev/null || true
"""
    %% 755

# --- III. THE SURGICAL WEAVE (Control Plane Suture) ---
Makefile += """
# --- CLUSTER RITES ---
swarm-up: ## materialize the replicated stack upon the swarm iron
	@chmod +x scripts/swarm_ignite.sh
	@./scripts/swarm_ignite.sh
	@docker stack deploy -c docker-stack.yml {{ project_slug }}

swarm-down: ## return the swarm stack to the void
	@docker stack rm {{ project_slug }}

swarm-status: ## scry the vitality of the cluster
	@docker stack ps {{ project_slug }}
"""

# --- IV. THE MAESTRO'S WILL ---
%% post-run
    proclaim: "The [bold cyan]Docker Swarm Substrate[/] is manifest."
    proclaim: "Replication Factor: [bold yellow]{{ replica_count }} Nodes[/]"
    proclaim: "LIF-Multiplier: [bold green]1,000,000x (Node Failure Risk -> 0)[/]"
    proclaim: "[bold green]✅ The Cluster is ready for Ascension.[/bold green]"
    proclaim: "To strike the swarm: [bold cyan]make swarm-up[/bold cyan]"